# NTFS Permissions

## Objective

Configure and validate NTFS permissions to control access to files and folders within an Active Directory environment.

# Environment

- Windows Server 2022
- Active Directory Domain Services
- Domain Users and Security Groups

# Tasks Performed

- Created shared folders on SERVER1
- Assigned NTFS permissions to users and groups
- Configured inherited and explicit permissions
- Tested access using multiple user accounts
- Verified permission enforcement through Windows Explorer and command-line tools

# Key Concepts

## Inherited Permissions

Inherited permissions were used to simplify administration and maintain consistent access controls throughout the folder hierarchy.

## Explicit Permissions

Explicit permissions were applied when unique access requirements existed for specific folders or users.

## Principle of Least Privilege

Access was granted only to the resources required for a user’s role, reducing unnecessary permissions and improving security.

## Validation

Permission configurations were tested by:

- Logging in as different users
- Attempting authorized file access
- Attempting unauthorized file access
- Verifying successful and denied operations

